Mamelodi Sundowns striker Jeremy Brockie has just made an important announcement that will change his life. The towering New Zelander‚ who has spent more time on the sidelines and on the stands than on the pitch in recent months‚ took to Twitter on Tuesday morning to announce to his social media followers that he has been "scoring more" at home. "What happens when you keep a striker in the stands for too long?" he asked. "He starts scoring more at home. "My beautiful wife is 16 weeks pregnant." The 31-year-old footballer and his wife Jessica Passmore are already parents to two kids - and the new arrival will expand their family to five.